TI  - Position Note on Economic Aspects of Climate Change
T2  - UNDP
AB  - This position note explains the need to align macro-level and micro-level policies to avoid massive climate change and explores specific policy instruments to do so. It stresses that a globally stable solution requires a critical mass of actors and “changing the rules of the game”. It notes that the choice we face is whether we take action at still relatively low cost and while the severe effects are still reversible, or act only later at much higher cost and when room for maneuver is severely diminished.
LA  - en
UR  - https://www.undp.org/publications/position-note-economic-aspects-climate-change
